content:
For compliance reasons, Salesforce admins can delete a customer’s personal identifiable information (PII) from enhanced Messaging channels and Messaging for In-App and Web channels. The PII is removed when their messaging user records and all associated conversations are deleted.

Available in: Lightning Experience.
This article applies to: Messaging for In-App, Messaging for Web, enhanced WhatsApp, enhanced Facebook Messenger, enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel.
This article doesn’t apply to: Standard WhatsApp, standard Facebook Messenger, and standard SMS channels

To delete enhanced Messaging conversations:

* Go to the messaging user record found in the Messaging Users tab or Messaging Users related list.
* Close any open conversations associated with the messaging user.
* As an admin, log in to Omni-Channel.
* Scroll to the Messaging Sessions related list on the messaging user record.
* Find a messaging session whose action menu shows the Close Conversation action. Click Close Conversation to close the conversation and its related messaging sessions.
* Execute a SOQL query to get the messaging session record’s parent Conversation record ID.
* Contact Salesforce Customer Support, provide the Conversation record ID, and ask them to delete the Conversation record.
* Refresh the page showing the Messaging Sessions related list. Messaging sessions that were part of the newly deleted conversation no longer appear in the list.
* Delete the messaging user record.

Required user permissions: End Messaging Session
title: Deleting Messaging Customer Data
